Please encourage your kids to take advantage of this great opportunity.

Welcome: Cyril Elementary: Return to Learn
Cyril Elementary has been planning for the 2020-2021 school year. We feel we have developed a plan for learning that provides your child with a safe and healthy environment. One that supports quality instruction to help your child be successful. We are excited for a new school year here at CES.
We strongly believe that direct instruction is the best instruction; however, we understand that some parents may not be comfortable with their child returning to a traditional setting at this time. Therefore, Cyril Elementary will be offering both traditional instruction with students attending classes as previous years, as well as virtual learning. Below… More

post_text: Yesterday, May 14th, was suppose to be CES family fun day; a day so many of us look forward to; today is our last day of the 2019-2020 school year. A day where friends would say their good-byes to their teachers and to one another until the new year. How quickly things changed! I just want to take a moment to thank my staff for your adjustments, your dedication and commitment, and mostly for your genuine love for your students. It is such an honor to work with each of you; you inspire me! Students, I MISS your smiles, your compliments, your hugs (even though on pancake day I go home with sticky clothes.) LOL Mrs. Cocheran can hardly wait for 'morning greetings' next year! Parents, … More

post_text: Parents, I hope all is going well at home with your child's education. I have contacted teachers and they have reassured me that all students have been contacted and either on line learning or teaching packets have been made available to all students. Let's work as a team in providing our kids with a valuable education before breaking for summer. Please encourage your child to do work daily and then make sure that it is submitted to the teacher for scoring by the assigned date. We can do this! Please contact the staff if any help is needed. Have a great Easter and stay safe.

post_text: Good morning CES!! Today school starts back. Teachers and administrators have been working diligently the past couple of weeks reaching out to families and getting email addresses and phone numbers and contacting all parents to see whether their child would rather do on-line or paper learning packets. Hopefully, all goes well today as you start on an unexpected journey. I miss morning greetings, morning assembly, and just hanging out with you kids all day. Work hard, study, and be respectful to your teachers AKA parents over the next month. If you have problems with anything, please contact your teacher for help. Have a blessed day.

post_text: Thank you. thank you, thank you to all the parents and students of CES for the super nice compliments about Cyril Public Schools food service. We have had zero complaints and tons of nice things said about what is being delivered and how it is being delivered. It is absolutely wonderful to hear positive things in a negative circumstance. I want to send a special thanks to our lunch ladies for their great choices of food items; thank you to the Baptist church, Family Life church, and The Assembly for driving their vans and helping us get the food delivered. Please give me a call if we have missed anyone in our school district. I live by the saying, " Appreciate everything...expect nothing" and it is so refreshing to live around and work with others who feel the same way. It is a pleasure serving you all.

My goal is to always provide a safe , fun, friendly, educational environment for ALL students. It is the end of the school year and we have some issues which always seem to arise at this time as parents, kids, and staff are anxious for summer vacation. Please help us to create the greatest experience as possible for our students and teachers.

Parents, we welcome you. However, please do not linger in the halls, cafeteria, classrooms, etc. before, during , or after school hours. Kids are easily distracted when visitors are in the building and we want them to be on task and engaged in learning as much as possible.

Mandy Gray is with RandyandTammy Cocheran and 2 others.
February 27 at 10:29 PM ·

CONGRATULATIONS SHAYLYNN MCCLURE & ABIGAIL TURNER!!!

Every year I get to take 2 of my elementary students art to the Oklahoma State Capital for the OAEA State Superintendent Show so this week I had my 6th graders create ANY kind of art they wanted...acrylic, watercolor, pencil drawings, etc. let me tell you this year was our hardest decision ever! I picked one plate weaving and one artwork and so the two lucky students who were chosen this year were....SHAYLYNN MCCLURE & ABIGAIL TURNER!!!! You can see their work displayed at the State Capital building in the Education Bldg until April 3, 2020 when there will be an awards ceremony and reception. Here are their pieces of artwork. I will post all of my kids work tomorrow!
